			<description><![CDATA[<p>
We&#39;re seeking a highly motivated Senior Accountant/Accounting Manager to be responsible for managing accounts payable, payroll and general ledger related accounting duties. The accountant will be a key member of a small, high-functioning Finance team. The ideal candidate will be adaptable to a fast-paced and dynamic environment, and will be willing to take on responsibilities outside of his/her main area of expertise. Opportunities abound for the curious and engaged individual.</p>
<p>
<br />
DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES INCLUDE, BUT ARE NOT LIMITED TO:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Manage / oversee general accounting transactions, monthly close process and financial statement preparation</li>
<li>
Manage accounts payable, payroll, timesheets, expense report processing, and other accounting activities</li>
<li>
Prepare monthly government billing and annual Incurred Costs report</li>
<li>
Assist in internal financial reporting and analysis of operating expenses and actual versus budget comparisons</li>
<li>
Assist in year-end audits, tax returns and interface directly with the Company&rsquo;s external auditors</li>
<li>
Assist in identifying accounting issues and ensuring proper accounting treatment</li>
<li>
Ensure compliance on all tax filings and assist in preparation of government audit requests</li>
<li>
Perform ad hoc and special projects</li>
</ul>
<p>
EDUCATION / EXPERIENCE REQUIREMENTS:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Bachelors or Masters degree in accounting required</li>
<li>
Life Sciences industry experience required</li>
<li>
4+ years of strong accounting experience including exposure to complex/technical accounting matters</li>
<li>
Experience working with ERP systems (Microsoft Dynamics SL a plus)</li>
<li>
Experience with or strong interest in learning government contractor reporting is required</li>
<li>
Ability to multi-task, manage projects, and meet deadlines</li>
<li>
Must have strong MS Excel skills</li>
</ul>
<p>
OTHER QUALIFICATIONS:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Must be highly reliable with an ability to work with independence.</li>
<li>
Flexibility to work in a growing company with changes in responsibilities to meet the needs of the organization</li>
</ul>
